// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception
//
// test/audited/cpu16_iverilog.test — M7 US4 per-cell regression
// fixture for (cpu16 × iverilog). Per
// `specs/011-m7-driver-e2e/contracts/audited-corpus.contract.md`
// §5.
//
// **State (Phase 6 scaffold, 2026-05-12)**: this cell
// UNSUPPORTED-outs in the `:dev` container because iverilog is
// not on PATH. The cell turns into a real test once Phase 2A
// (the `:dev-m7` container PR) lands.
//
// **Goldens (Phase 5 final dependency)**: this cell runs `nslc
// -emit=verilog` + iverilog + vcd_diff against
// `test/audited/cpu16/golden/cpu16_basic.vcd`. That golden does
// not yet exist (Phase 5 T062 produces it from the upstream NSL
// toolchain). Pre-Phase-5-final the cell also fails on missing-
// golden in the vcd_diff step; the REQUIRES iverilog directive
// alone is sufficient to UNSUPPORTED at this stage.

// REQUIRES: iverilog

// 1. Emit split-file Verilog into a per-cell temp directory.
// RUN: rm -rf %t-verilog && mkdir -p %t-verilog
// RUN: %nslc -emit=verilog %S/cpu16/cpu.nsl -o %t-verilog/

// 2. Compile emitted Verilog + the project's simulation harness
//    under iverilog (-g2012 SystemVerilog).
// RUN: iverilog -g2012 -o %t.vvp %t-verilog/*.v %S/cpu16/cpu_sim.nsl

// 3. Run the simulation, capturing VCD to a per-cell temp file.
// RUN: cd %T && vvp %t.vvp +VCDFILE=%t.vcd

// 4. Compare captured VCD against the golden (Phase 5 T062 lands
//    the golden; vcd_diff signal-map optional).
// RUN: %vcd-diff %S/cpu16/golden/cpu16_basic.vcd %t.vcd
